//  2. Live source: [Customization point] Replace fetchRawItems() with your API/database calls.
//     The crawl.ts timer function uses fetchRawItems() + enhance() for production ingestion.
//
// FAIL CLOSED: raw items that fail enhancement are NEVER ingested.
// See src/functions/crawl.ts for the fail-closed enforcement pattern.
//
// Incremental sync (TODO):
//   To implement incremental sync, replace JsonlDataSource with a live data source that
//   accepts a `since: Date` parameter and returns only changed items. A sample pattern:
//
//     async *fetchModifiedSince(since: Date): AsyncIterable<RawItem> {
//       const response = await fetch(`${baseUrl}/items?modifiedSince=${since.toISOString()}`);
//       // ... yield changed items
